In his last attempt to avoid going to prison, Former President Jacob Zuma has launched another legal fight. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma's preparing to head to court again, to avoid going to prison. Zuma wants the Pietermaritzburg High Court to stop Police Minister Bheki Cele from arresting him until the Constitutional Court has heard his new application. READ: Cele seeks clarity on Zuma arrest order The Apex Court sentenced Zuma to 15 months in prison for failing to appear before the State Capture Commission of Inquiry. He was given five days to go to prison on his own or face arrest by police. eNCA senior reporter Siphamandla Goge shares more details in the video above.